      "contentSections": [
        {
          "type": "comparison",
          "title": "Three Program Tiers",
          "content": "QMB (up to $1,325/month single): Covers all Medicare premiums, deductibles, and copayments. SLMB ($1,326-$1,585/month single): Covers Medicare Part B premiums only. QI ($1,586-$1,781/month single): Covers Medicare Part B premiums only, but funding is limited."
        }
      ],
      "faqs": [
        {
          "question": "Can my parent have all three programs at once?",
          "answer": "No — these are three income tiers of the same program. Your parent will qualify for the highest tier their income allows. QMB provides the most benefits, QI provides the least."
        },
        {
          "question": "What happens if my parent's house is worth more than the asset limit?",
          "answer": "The primary home doesn't count toward the $9,660/$14,470 asset limits. Only countable assets like bank accounts, investments, and additional property matter for eligibility."
        },
        {
          "question": "Will SLMB or QI help with Medicare deductibles and copays?",
          "answer": "No — only QMB covers deductibles and copayments. SLMB and QI only pay the Medicare Part B premium ($174.70/month in 2026). If your parent has high medical costs, QMB provides much greater value."
        },
        {
          "question": "How often does my parent need to reapply?",
          "answer": "Income limits change every April 1st based on federal poverty levels, so annual renewal is typically required. Kentucky will send renewal notices, but families should track income changes throughout the year."
        },
        {
          "question": "Can I apply on behalf of my elderly parent?",
          "answer": "Yes, adult children can help with applications or apply as authorized representatives. You'll need to provide documentation showing you're authorized to act on their behalf."
        },
        {
          "question": "What if the QI program runs out of money?",
          "answer": "QI uses finite federal block grant funding that can be exhausted during the year. Apply early in January for the best chance of approval. QMB and SLMB don't have this funding limitation."
        }
      ],
