      "id": "energy-assistance-liheap",
      "name": "Kentucky Energy Assistance Program (LIHEAP)",
      "shortName": "Kentucky LIHEAP",
      "tagline": "Help paying heating and cooling bills if your parent's income is low and they're facing high energy costs",
      "programType": "benefit",
      "complexity": "medium",
      "geographicScope": {
        "type": "state"
      },
      "intro": "If your parent struggles to pay heating or cooling bills on a fixed income, Kentucky's LIHEAP program provides direct payments to utility companies to help cover energy costs. The program offers both regular seasonal assistance (typically November-December for heating) and crisis help when your parent faces disconnection or has run out of fuel.\n\nYour parent may qualify if household income is at or below 150% of the Federal Poverty Level and they have less than $2,000 in liquid assets. Because funds are distributed first-come, first-served until depleted, applying early in the season increases chances of receiving assistance.\n\nThe program operates through 23 Community Action Agencies across all 120 Kentucky counties. Crisis assistance runs January 6-March 27 in some areas, while summer cooling assistance may be available if funds remain after winter distributions.",
